FBIS3-22074 "jptdd013__l94077" JPRS-tdd-94-013-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Narcotics 21 March 1994 NEAR EAST & SOUTH ASIA PAKISTAN `Guest' of Indian Intelligence Service Arrested With 92 Kg of Precursor BK2103114994 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in English 1100 GMT 21 Mar 94 BK2103114994 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network Language: English Article Type:BFN [Text] The Federal Investigation Agency has seized at the Lahore railway station 92 kg of acetic anhydride sent by Indian intelligence for manufacture of narcotics in the tribal areas. This was stated by the interior minister, retired Major General Nasirullah Khan Babar, at a news conference in Islamabad today. He said the carrier of the drug, Mohammad Imran, a Pakistani who was guest of Indian intelligence agency in Amritsar, has been arrested along with the chemical. The interior minister asked the international community to take notice of the Indian activities of encouraging the manufacture of heroin in Pakistan.
